<p><a href="#sdfootnote33anc" name="sdfootnote33sym">33</a><sup></sup> This anonymity grants them the status traditionally reserved for state witnesses or secret operatives. The former narrative can be found in<em> Dark Content</em>, wherein moderators are given virtual avatars to hide behind, thus shielding them from the potentially harmful consequences of their custodial work. <em>The Cleaners</em>, on the other hand, brings up associations with covert operatives striving to save the world, or a secret brotherhood working behind the scenes to guard a sacred order. The smothering, secretive atmosphere of the narrative, blurry images, and darkened frames may bring to mind stories of people forced into hiding. Fragments of e-mails appearing on the screen, meanwhile, seem to be a trope taken straight from a spy movie.</p>
